-- EARNINGS POLL-Poland's PZU Q1 net profit seen down on lower premiums
-- 
-- Thu May 08, 2014 04:27AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, May 8 (Reuters) - Eastern Europe's largest insurer PZU <PZU.WA> is seen reporting a 7-percent fall in its first-quarter net profit due to a dip in the Polish group's written premiums, a Reuters survey showed on Thursday.

The state-controlled insurer is expected to show a bottom line of 781 million zlotys ($259.5 million), with gross written premiums seen 2.4-percent down at 4.318 billion, based on the average of estimates from eight banks and brokerages. Written premiums are the premiums on insurance policies written during a given period. The following table summarises market forecasts for PZU: (Figures in millions of zlotys unless stated). FIRST QUARTER OF 2014  Net profit  Gross written